# VSpot ClipboardApp - Claude Project Configuration

## Project Context
This is a macOS SwiftUI clipboard manager app designed for the menubar with App Store compliance.

## Current Status
- **Phase 1**: ✅ Complete (MenuBar Foundation & Setup)
- **Phase 2**: ✅ Complete (Core Clipboard Functionality) 
- **Phase 3**: ⚠️ ~75% Complete (Notes Functionality)
- **Phase 4**: ⚠️ ~60% Complete (Customizable Tabs)
- **Phase 5**: ❌ Not Started (App Store Compliance)

## Key Architecture
- **Framework**: SwiftUI + MenuBarExtra for macOS 13.0+
- **Structure**: MVVM pattern with ObservableObject ViewModels
- **Icon**: Custom "v" branding with PNG assets in all sizes
- **Storage**: UserDefaults (planning Core Data migration)

## Main Components
- `ClipboardAppApp.swift` - Main app entry with MenuBarExtra
- `MenuBarContentView.swift` - Primary menubar interface
- `ClipboardManager.swift` - Clipboard monitoring and management
- `NotesManager.swift` - Sticky notes functionality
- `PasteboardService.swift` - System clipboard integration

## Current Working Features
- ✅ Real-time clipboard monitoring
- ✅ Searchable clipboard history
- ✅ Color-coded sticky notes
- ✅ Custom tabs system
- ✅ MenuBar integration

## Next Priorities
1. Complete Phase 3 & 4 remaining tasks
2. Implement App Store compliance (Phase 5)
3. Add proper encryption for sensitive data
4. Create privacy policy and landing page

## Development Notes
- Use existing PNG icon assets in Assets.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset/
- All data stored locally for privacy
- No external network calls (App Store compliant)
- Proper entitlements configured for clipboard access
